Heat olive oil and 1 tablespoon butter in large nonstick skillet over medium heat until butter melts starts to bubble. Add chops to skillet and cook 8 to 10 minutes, turning once. Remove chops and cover to keep warm. Melt remaining 2 tablespoons butter in skillet. Cook apples and onion in butter 3 to 5 minutes, stirring occasionally, or until onions are tender. Add water and bring to a boil. Stir in stuffing mix. Remove from heat. Nestle chops into stuffing and let stand 5 minutes before serving.